headline: Why The Nasdaq (NDAQ) Story Is Shifting As Analyst Targets Cluster Above US$110
summary: The fair value price target for Nasdaq has been nudged lower from US$108.33 to US$107.73, a small adjustment that still sits close to where many analysts now cluster in the low to mid US$110s. Even as the consolidated Street target edges down slightly, several firms are lifting individual targets into the US$113 to US$120 range and keeping positive ratings in place.
